_:B9a12bd09476732f5ae314b9cf11807b1 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "The term leg can mean: [1] an appendage on which an animal walks [2] the entire hindlimb of a tetrapod [3] the segment of a human leg between knee and ankle (cf FMA) [4] the region of a hindlimb include the stylopod and zeugopod, but excluding the autopod. We define this class as [4], and thus 'leg' is compltely analagous to 'arm'. For [1], see the class 'locomotive weight-bearing appendage'. For [2] we use 'hindlimb'. For" .
_:B9a12bd09476732f5ae314b9cf11807b1 <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#source> "3" .
